    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.002 Hitler, Adolf/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 6, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Your 48 March 6, noon. I have been in frequent touch recently with the German
                    Ambassador regarding the proposed mock trial.</p>
                <p>After careful study I informed Doctor Luther on March 2, that the participants
                    were acting as individuals and not in any sense as representing the Federal
                    Government; that no legal authority could be <pb facs="0612" n="512"
                        xml:id="pg_512"/> found that would enable the Federal Government to instruct
                    the participants to refrain from the demonstration contemplated; and that no law
                    clothed the Federal Government with any authority to compel its abandonment.</p>
                <p>I feel that any effort to intercede in this matter or to take official cognizance
                    of it would react disadvantageously.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
